{{nihongo|'''Masaru Furukawa'''|古川 勝|Furukawa Masaru|extra=born January 6, 1936 in [[Hashimoto, Wakayama]]}} is a [[Japanese people|Japanese]] [[swimming (sport)|swimmer]] and Olympic champion. He competed at the [[1956 Summer Olympics|1956 Olympic Games]] in [[Melbourne]], where he received a gold medal in the 200&nbsp;m [[breaststroke swimming|breaststroke]].<ref name=db-olymp-1956SWI>[http://www.databaseolympics.com/games/gamessport.htm?g=14&sp=SWI "1956 Olympics &ndash; Melbourne, Australia &ndash; Swimming"] &ndash; ''databaseOlympics.com'' (Retrieved on September 5, 2008)</ref>

==World records==
Furukawa improved the [[World record progression 200 metres breaststroke|world record of 200 metres breaststroke]] (long course) four times in 1954 and 1955, and his last record lasted until 1958.

==Awards==
Furukawa was inducted into the [[International Swimming Hall of Fame]] in 1981.

